        "text": "Post by reinafu on\n\nMost of his roles were bad guys' roles and he was very good in playing these characters. I also saw him playing good guys (such as in The winged tiger from the Shaws', if I'm not mistaken (I saw so many movies !!))and he was as good as when he played bad guys.\n\nPost by machete on\n\nAlthough he had already passed away in 2009 and not recently, I thought I might make a thread dedicated to the State of Divinity 1996 Zuo Leng Zan who was praised by reviewers for his role. Was he a popular actor with Shaw Brothers? When the TV channel airs reruns of Shaw Brothers movies ,I see his roles weren't that big (compared to Lo Lieh for example)before making it bigger in TVB dramas shows like State of Divinity 1996,Nan Quan Bei Tui(Fists of power)/Dark Tales and so on. But the Wikipedia entry says he had two prominent roles and rose to fame in Come Drink With Me so correct me if I'm wrong."
